          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make and blind-bake the pastry base",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 180°C fan. Rub the cold {{unsalted-butter}} into the {{plain-flour}}, {{caster-sugar}}, and {{fine-sea-salt}}. Mix in the egg yolk and enough cold water (1 to 2 teaspoons) for the dough to come together. Press into the base of a 23 cm springform tin (no need to roll). Line with baking paper and fill with baking weights. Bake for 15 minutes, then remove the weights and bake for 5 more minutes. This is the base only; the sides of the sernik are set by the filling. Reduce the oven to 160°C.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the filling and bake, 55 to 65 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the {{quark}} (the closest available substitute for ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "twaróg",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpaqcb2q000068v41mzwzjjs"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ") with 150 g of the {{caster-sugar}}, the egg yolks, melted {{unsalted-butter}}, {{plain-flour}}, {{vanilla-extract}}, and {{lemon-juice}} until smooth. Fold in the {{sultanas}} if using. In a separate clean bowl, beat the egg whites to soft peaks, then add the remaining 25 g of {{caster-sugar}} and beat to firm peaks. Fold one-third of the egg whites into the quark mixture to loosen it, then fold in the remaining two-thirds. Pour over the pre-baked pastry base. Bake at 160°C for 55 to 65 minutes until the edges are set but the centre still has a slight wobble. Turn the oven off, open the door ajar, and leave for 30 minutes. Cool completely, then refrigerate for at least 4 hours. Dust with {{icing-sugar}} and serve at room temperature.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
